This course gives an overview of the process of social research: from research design to data collection, to quantitative and qualitative data analysis and interpretation of results. It outlines the ways, how to gather data, revising different method's strengths and weaknesses. Data analyse topics range over quantitative and qualitative approaches and combine practical considerations with philosophical issues.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Course will give students knowledge and skills of the main quantitative and qualitative research and data analysis methods in the field of economics and social sciences and give experiences of applying these methods in solving different research questions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students who have passed the course have acquired: * Knowledge about the nature of scientific research and specifics of economics and business research, about different research strategies and design, as well about stages of the research process; * Knowledge about qualitative and quantitative data gathering and analysis methods; * Skills how to apply different qualitative and quantitative data gathering and analysis methods; * Skills how to interpret and generalize results of data analysis and how to present research findings.
